   },
   {
    "page": 8,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@12/center",
    "text": "by His Holiness The Fourteenth Dalai Lama"
   },
   {
    "page": 10,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "In the Name of God, the Compassionate, the Merciful"
   },
   {
    "page": 10,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "May Peace and Blessings be upon the Prophet Muhammad"
   },
   {
    "page": 10,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Introduction to Common Ground"
   },
   {
    "page": 10,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@12/center",
    "text": "By H. R. H. Prince Ghazi bin Muhammad"
   },
   {
    "page": 10,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The Religions of the World and World Peace"
   },
   {
    "page": 11,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Why Do We Need ‘Common Ground’?"
   },
   {
    "page": 13,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "The Common Ground"
   },
   {
    "page": 14,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "and that through Mercy we are saved and delivered)."
   },
   {
    "page": 14,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "He hath ordained for you that religion which He commend-"
   },
   {
    "page": 14,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "ed unto Noah, and that which We inspire in thee (Muham-"
   },
   {
    "page": 15,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "People of the Scripture (Ahl Al-Kitab)"
   },
   {
    "page": 16,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "truth which hath come unto thee. For each We have ap-"
   },
   {
    "page": 17,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "Earlier Common Ground ?"
   },
   {
    "page": 17,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "And all praise be to God, the Lord of the worlds."
   },
   {
    "page": 18,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Preface"
   },
   {
    "page": 18,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@12/center",
    "text": "by Professor Mohammad Hashim Kamali"
   },
   {
    "page": 23,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Acknowledgements"
   },
   {
    "page": 24,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@30/center",
    "text": "Common Ground"
   },
   {
    "page": 24,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@26/center",
    "text": "Between"
   },
   {
    "page": 24,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@30/center",
    "text": "Islam and Buddhism"
   },
   {
    "page": 26,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Part One"
   },
   {
    "page": 26,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Setting the Scene"
   },
   {
    "page": 26,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Beyond the Letter to the Spirit"
   },
   {
    "page": 32,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "A Glance at History"
   },
   {
    "page": 37,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Qur’ānic Premises of Dialogue"
   },
   {
    "page": 38,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "return, and He will inform you of that about which you dif-"
   },
   {
    "page": 38,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "• Truly We inspire you, as We inspired Noah, and the proph-"
   },
   {
    "page": 38,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "[saying]: There is no God save Me, so worship Me. (21:25)"
   },
   {
    "page": 39,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The Buddha as Messenger"
   },
   {
    "page": 40,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "death is suffering; sorrow, lamentation, pain, grief, and de-"
   },
   {
    "page": 40,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "spair are suffering; not to obtain what one wants is suffer-"
   },
   {
    "page": 40,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "and delights in this and that; that is, craving for sensual plea-"
   },
   {
    "page": 40,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "derless fading away and ceasing, the giving up, relinquish-"
   },
   {
    "page": 41,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "And what is the way leading to the cessation of suffer-"
   },
   {
    "page": 42,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "the body, after death, have reappeared in a state of depriva-"
   },
   {
    "page": 42,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "of the body, after death, have reappeared in a good destina-"
   },
   {
    "page": 42,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "ugly, fortunate and unfortunate, and I understood how be-"
   },
   {
    "page": 44,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Revelation from on High or Within?"
   },
   {
    "page": 48,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "world of gods and men—means adapted to their tempera-"
   },
   {
    "page": 48,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "leader regardless of his nationality and professed creed, Ma-"
   },
   {
    "page": 48,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "hayanists recognized a Buddha in Socrates, Mohammad, Je-"
   },
   {
    "page": 48,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "sus, Francis of Assisi, Confucius, Laotze, and many others.28"
   },
   {
    "page": 49,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The Dalai Lama and the Dynamics of Dialogue"
   },
   {
    "page": 50,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Buddha, Jesus Christ, Muhammad and Moses, were moti-"
   },
   {
    "page": 52,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "better with people from other religious traditions and cul-"
   },
   {
    "page": 52,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "have seen this value from within your own tradition.35"
   },
   {
    "page": 52,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "People often experience feelings of exclusivity in their reli-"
   },
   {
    "page": 52,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "path—which can create a sense of apprehension about con-"
   },
   {
    "page": 52,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "greater our awareness is regarding the value and effective-"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Part Two"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Oneness: The Highest"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Common Denominator"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Conceiving of the One"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "There is, monks, an unborn, not become, not made, uncom-"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "pounded; and were it not, monks, for this unborn, not be-"
   },
   {
    "page": 54,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "here for what is born, has become, is made, is compounded."
   },
   {
    "page": 55,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "But those who know the Real is, and know the unreal"
   },
   {
    "page": 60,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "‘Everything exists’—this, Kaccāyana, is one extreme. ‘Ev-"
   },
   {
    "page": 60,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "erything does not exist’—this, Kaccāyana, is the second ex-"
   },
   {
    "page": 62,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "All things have no provenance and no one can create them:"
   },
   {
    "page": 64,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 74,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Hence one of them says, “I am the Real!” (anā’l-Haqq), an-"
   },
   {
    "page": 76,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 76,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "This dharma which the Tathāgata has fully known or dem-"
   },
   {
    "page": 78,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "will stand firmly in suchness, or that will know this full en-"
   },
   {
    "page": 78,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Therefore, O Sariputra, it is because of his nonattainment-"
   },
   {
    "page": 82,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "They ask you of the Hour: when will it come to pass? Why—"
   },
   {
    "page": 82,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "what can you say about it? Unto your Lord belongs [know-"
   },
   {
    "page": 83,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Worship of the One"
   },
   {
    "page": 94,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "of the self; a holy freedom through the melting of our self-"
   },
   {
    "page": 94,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "power (jiriki) in the Other Power (tariki), through the sur-"
   },
   {
    "page": 102,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 104,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Part Three"
   },
   {
    "page": 104,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Ethics of Detachment"
   },
   {
    "page": 104,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "and Compassion"
   },
   {
    "page": 104,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Detachment: Anicca and Zuhd"
   },
   {
    "page": 107,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Be in this world as if you were a stranger or a wayfarer.3"
   },
   {
    "page": 107,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The heart of an old man remains young in two respects:"
   },
   {
    "page": 107,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "If the son of Adam [i.e., the human being] had two val-"
   },
   {
    "page": 107,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The fire of hell is veiled by passionate desires, while"
   },
   {
    "page": 107,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Remember much that which ends all pleasures (hādhim"
   },
   {
    "page": 108,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Short indeed is this life. This side of a hundred years it per-"
   },
   {
    "page": 108,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "mine own”. So seeing, let not one devote himself to selfish-"
   },
   {
    "page": 110,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "iron, of wood or of rope; much stronger is the fetter of pas-"
   },
   {
    "page": 110,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "own’. So seeing, let not one devote himself to selfishness."
   },
   {
    "page": 117,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Loving Compassion: Karunā and Rahma"
   },
   {
    "page": 118,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT@11/center",
    "text": "Unto each, the former and the latter, do We extend the gra-"
   },
   {
    "page": 120,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "above, below, and all around without limit. So let him cul-"
   },
   {
    "page": 120,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "tivate a boundless good will towards the entire world, un-"
   },
   {
    "page": 126,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 126,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "going to the Uncompounded. Now what, brethren, is the Un-"
   },
   {
    "page": 134,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 135,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "Epilogue"
   },
   {
    "page": 135,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "The Common Ground of Sanctity"
   },
   {
    "page": 135,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The mingling of both [wisdom and compassion] is"
   },
   {
    "page": 136,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "which may not be reckoned, so great is its diversity’.1"
   },
   {
    "page": 137,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "* * *"
   },
   {
    "page": 138,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@18/center",
    "text": "%XGGKD\u0003LQ\u0003WKH\u00034XU¶ƗQ\""
   },
   {
    "page": 138,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@12/center",
    "text": "by Shaykh Hamza Yusuf"
   },
   {
    "page": 140,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 142,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "(UXKƗQL\\\\ƯQ) and taking intercessors. When they were un-"
   },
   {
    "page": 142,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "the Sabians of Asia Minor relied upon planets, and the Sabi-"
   },
   {
    "page": 142,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "benefit anyone one iota. The first group consists of worship-"
   },
   {
    "page": 142,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "the Kaaba, for example, is exalted [among Muslims].11"
   },
   {
    "page": 143,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 144,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Based upon their description of the Buddha, if they are ac-"
   },
   {
    "page": 146,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "The Prophet \u000e is reported to have said concerning al-Khad-"
   },
   {
    "page": 147,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 148,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "[The Ummayyad governors] allowed followers of non-Mus-"
   },
   {
    "page": 148,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "functioning. The Han Chinese pilgrim Yijing (I-Ching) vis-"
   },
   {
    "page": 149,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "An Umayyad Arab author, al-Kermani, wrote a detailed"
   },
   {
    "page": 152,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 154,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "-L]\\DK is taken from the Arab idolaters and whoever prac-"
   },
   {
    "page": 154,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "worshipers of idols or fire given that the Prophet \u000e him-"
   },
   {
    "page": 154,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "\u000e took ML]\\DK from the Magians of Hajar and Oman. Fur-"
   },
   {
    "page": 154,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "were Buddhists as well as the majority who were Zoroas-"
   },
   {
    "page": 156,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 159,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "***"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Abraham \u0005 replies, “Because he was an idolater.”"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "³*RG\u0003DVNV\u0003\\RX\u000f\u0003µ'LG\u0003\\RX\u0003FUHDWH\u0003KLP\u0003RU\u0003GLG\u0003,\"¶´\u0003"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Abraham \u0005 replies, “Of course, You created him.”"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "³*RG\u0003DVNV\u0003\\RX\u000f\u0003µ:DV\u0003KLV\u0003GLVEHOLHI\u0003LQ\u00030H\u0003RU\u0003LQ\u0003\\RX\"¶´\u0003"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "Abraham \u0005 responds, “His disbelief was in You.”"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "0\\\u0003VHUYDQW\u0003DQG\u0003\\RXU\u0003EURWKHU\"\u0003)RU\u0003KH\u0003LV\u0003LQ\u0003RQH\u0003RI\u0003WZR\u0003SRV-"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "him. The man said, “Something happened, as you are act-"
   },
   {
    "page": 160,
    "pstyle": "TimesNewRomanPSMT@11/center",
    "text": "now you are showing me kindness, as if you want some-"
